    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is a collector-grade 2010 Porsche 911 Carrera S (997.2). This specimen is powered by the 3.8L MA101 Direct Fuel Injection (DFI) flat-six, delivering a linear 385 hp through a tactile G97/05 6-speed manual transaxle. The chassis is equipped with Porsche Active Suspension Management (PASM) and the Sport Chrono Package Plus, ensuring precision damping and optimized throttle mapping. Meticulously maintained, the vehicle shows zero seepage at the rear main seal and a clean DME report with no ignition over-revs in higher stages. The factory finish retains consistent micron depth across all panels, and the interior features supple leather with no bolster compression or UV degradation. This is a mechanically superlative example of the final hydraulic-steering Carrera, offered in turn-key condition.",
